article.headline: Sam Houston St. 91, Texas Arlington 81
article.story: HUNTSVILLE, Texas (AP) -- Chris Jordan scored 24 points, including 10-of-11 from the free-throw line, to lead Sam Houston State to a 91-81 win over Texas-Arlington on Saturday night. JeJuan Plair added 18 points and Aaron Wade had 14 for the Bearkats (14-5, 5-2 Southland). Jarrett Howell scored 23 points to lead Texas-Arlington (11-9, 4-3). Kenneth Henderson added 14 points for the Mavericks. Jermaine Griffin scored 11 and Steven Thomas had 10. Sam Houston led 43-31 at halftime.
